'''Saud Abdullah Salem Abdulhamid''' ({{langx|ar|سُعُود عَبْد الله سَالِم عَبْد الْحَمِيد}}; born 18 July 1999) is a Saudi Arabian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[RC Lens|Lens]], and the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=سعود عبدالحميد – Saud Abdulhamid |url=http://www.kooora.com/?player=143770 |access-date=3 January 2019 |website=Kooora}}</ref>

He previously played for [[Saudi Pro League]] clubs [[Al-Ittihad Club (Jeddah)|Al-Ittihad]] and [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]].

==Club career==

=== Al-Ittihad and Al-Hilal ===
Abdulhamid started his career at [[Al-Ittihad Club (Jeddah)|Al-Ittihad]] before joining [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]] in 2022, where he achieved six domestic titles.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/sports/2024/09/06/saud-abdulhamid-to-roma-which-other-gulf-players-have-moved-to-europe |title=Saud Abdulhamid to Roma - which other Gulf players have moved to Europe? |publisher=Al Arabiya |date=6 September 2024 }}</ref>

===Roma===
On 27 August 2024, Abdulhamid signed for [[Serie A]] club [[AS Roma|Roma]] for €2.5 million.<ref>{{cite web |title=Saud Abdulhamid joins the Giallorossi |url=https://www.asroma.com/en/news/71737/saud-abdulhamid-joins-the-giallorossi |publisher=AS Roma |access-date=27 August 2024 |date=27 August 2024 }}</ref> A month later, on 26 September, he made his debut in a 1–1 draw against [[Athletic Bilbao]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]], becoming the first Saudi player to feature in European competitions.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ysscores.com/en/news/4680066/Saud-Abdul-Hamid-launches-his-first-participation-with-Roma |title=Saud Abdul Hamid launches his first participation with Roma |publisher=ysscores.com |date=27 September 2024 }}</ref> On 24 November, he made his Serie A debut as a substitute in a 1–0 away defeat against [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/saud-abdulhamid-makes-history-in-serie-a-with-as-roma-40353250 |title=Saud Abdulhamid makes history in Serie A with AS Roma |publisher=OneFootball |date=25 November 2024 }}</ref> A month later, on 12 December, Abdulhamid scored his first goal for Roma in a 3–0 win against [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] in the Europa League, becoming the first Saudi player to score in a European continental competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/saud-abdulhamid-becomes-first-saudi-player-to-score-in-european-competition-40431699 |title=Saud Abdulhamid becomes first Saudi player to score in European competition |publisher=OneFootball |date=12 December 2024 }}</ref>

===Lens===
On 3 August 2025, Abdulhamid joined [[Ligue 1]] club [[RC Lens|Lens]] on a one-year loan for the [[2025–26 RC Lens season|2025–26 season]], with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rclens.fr/fr/news/saud-abdulhamid-rclens-signature-mercato-20250803 |title=Saud Abdulhamid, à Bollaert dans son nouveau jardin |publisher=RC Lens |language=fr |date=3 August 2025 }}</ref> Later that year, on 19 December, he netted his first goal and provided an assist in a 3–1 victory over [[Entente Feignies Aulnoye FC|Feignies]] in the [[2025–26 Coupe de France|Coupe de France]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/762239/feignies-lens |title=Lens 3–1 Feignies |publisher=ESPN |date=19 December 2025 }}</ref> He scored his first league goal in a 3–0 win over [[FC Metz|Metz]] on 8 March 2026.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-mena/football/ligue-1/articles-video/lens-close-in-on-psg-with-win-over-lowly-metz-2026-03-08 |title=Lens close in on PSG with win over lowly Metz |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=8 March 2026 }}</ref> He eventually started in the [[2026 Coupe de France final|Coupe de France final]], helping his club secure the title with a 3–1 victory over [[OGC Nice|Nice]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://dailysports.net/news/saud-abdulhamid-makes-history/ |title=Saud Abdulhamid makes history |publisher=Dailysports |date=23 May 2026 }}</ref>

On 4 June 2026, Lens exercised the buy option in Abdulhamid's loan deal, making his move permanent and extending his contract until 2029.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rclens.fr/fr/saud-abdulhamid-prolongation-saudi-crush-20260604 |title=Saud Abdulhamid au Racing, la saga continue ! |publisher=RC Lens |language=fr |date=4 August 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Abdulhamid made his debut for the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]] in 2019 in a 1–1 draw against [[Mali national football team|Mali]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Saudi Arabia vs. Mali - 5 September 2019 |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/05/world/friendlies/saudi-arabia/mali/3147505/ |publisher=Soccerway |access-date=27 August 2024 |date=5 September 2019 }}</ref> He represented his country at the [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2020 Summer Olympics]],<ref name="Toyko2020">{{cite web |url=https://olympics.com/tokyo-2020/olympic-games/en/results/football/athlete-profile-n1484611-abdulhamid-saud.htm |title=ABDULHAMID Saud |publisher=[[Tokyo Organising Committee of the Olympic and Paralympic Games]] |access-date=2 September 2021}}</ref> [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], and [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]].

